  "SSPs only provide economic data without climate projections": "",
  "SSPs add socioeconomic context to emission pathways: SSP1 assumes sustainable development with strong institutions, while SSP3 assumes regional conflict and fragmentation; this matters because socioeconomic conditions determine both emission trajectories and society's ability to adapt.": "",
  "Climate models show that even with immediate cessation of all emissions, temperatures would not immediately return to pre-industrial levels. What concept explains this?": "",
  "Committed warming from ocean thermal inertia and the long atmospheric lifetime of CO2": "",
  "Natural variability would mask the cooling": "",
  "Solar radiation would prevent any cooling": "",
  "Climate models are inaccurate about temperature recovery": "",
  "Committed warming occurs because the ocean has absorbed enormous amounts of heat that will continue warming the atmosphere, and CO2 persists in the atmosphere for centuries; even stopping all emissions today, temperatures would remain elevated for decades to centuries.": "",
  "For an AP FRQ, a student is given a graph showing multiple model projections diverging after 2030 under different scenarios. How should the student explain this divergence?": "",
